<statement>
<p>
Suppose you are taking out a mortgage and you must pay two points on it. How much must be paid?</p>
<p><ol style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li><m>\displaystyle{1}\%</m> of the monthly payment</li> 
<li><m>\displaystyle{1}\%</m> of the mortgage amount</li> 
<li><m>\displaystyle{2}\%</m> of the down payment</li> 
<li><m>\displaystyle{3}\%</m> of the sale price</li> 
<li><m>\displaystyle{1}\%</m> of the sale price</li> 
<li><m>\displaystyle{3}\%</m> of the down payment</li> 
<li><m>\displaystyle{2}\%</m> of the monthly payment</li> 
<li><m>\displaystyle{1}\%</m> of the down payment</li> 
<li><m>\displaystyle{3}\%</m> of the monthly payment</li> 
<li><m>\displaystyle{3}\%</m> of the mortgage amount</li> 
<li><m>\displaystyle{2}\%</m> of the sale price</li> 
<li><m>\displaystyle{2}\%</m> of the mortgage amount</li> 
</ol></p>


</statement>
<answer>
<p><ul><li>L: <m>\displaystyle{2}\%</m> of the mortgage amount</li></ul></p>
</answer>

</myopenmath>